In PHP you can redirect like this:

    header(&quot;Location: thank-you.php&quot;);

In Javascript you can redirect like this:

    window.location.href = &#39;/thank-you.php&#39;;

If you want to do something on the page after the email is sent, but before the redirect, then you need to redirect via JS. Otherwise you can redirect via PHP. Since you have different forms and you want to redirect to different thank you pages, you could specify that in the backend, based on the kind of form which was sent.

you can use header location to redirect in php and use query string to send data back
   

     if(mail()) {
              header(&#39;Location: http://example.com?success=&#39;.$msg[&#39;success&#39;]);
            } else {
              echo &#39;Message was not sent.&#39;;
            }
     

On Thank you page just use below code to get message value

    if (isset($_GET[&#39;success&#39;])) {    
       echo $_GET[&#39;success&#39;];
    }

you can Also use sessions to send data across php pages.

